{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "14", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "09", "M": "43", "S": "34"}}, "news": [{"title": "As India's energy revolution accelerates, real estate stands to gain", "para": "Energy access is shifting from security to national sovereignty for nations. Real estate infrastructure converts energy potential into sustained economic value for India. Industrial parks and renewable energy facilities create economic epicenters and ecosystems. India's policy architecture supports energy ambition and infrastructure execution. Real estate is the ground for India's energy sovereignty and global standing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/indias-energy-revolution-a-boon-for-real-estate-development/132387107?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1398988/132387107.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "indias-energy-revolution-a-boon-for-real-estate-development"}, {"title": "Rajasthan: 86 colonies plan mahapanchayat over pending land titles", "para": "Residents of 86 colonies in Sanganer and Bagru are demanding land titles.  These families established their homes decades ago through cooperative societies.  They warn of boycotting local body elections if demands are unmet.  A mahapanchayat and public movement are planned if no decision occurs.  The Niyaman Hetu Sangharsh Samiti leads this ongoing community effort.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/rajasthan-colonies-threaten-election-boycott-over-land-title-issues/132386111?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1747617/132386111.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Mumbai: BMC plans to launch single portal for construction waste monitoring by July-end", "para": "Mumbai's BMC will launch an integrated construction and demolition waste management portal by July.  This new system aims to monitor all waste generated within the city.  A soil exchange platform will also be introduced for developers and contractors.  Government agencies and infrastructure projects will register on this single digital platform.  The portal will prevent illegal dumping and ensure waste accountability across Mumbai.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/bmc-to-launch-state-of-the-art-portal-for-construction-waste-management-in-mumbai-by-july-end/132385582?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1598961/132385582.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}]}